MATCH_TOOL: Write|Edit
MATCH_PATTERN: \.claude/guardrails/.*\.rule
ADVISORY: |
  You are creating or editing a guardrail rule file.

  Pattern matching should be SPECIFIC, not broad:
  ❌ MATCH_PATTERN: server\.ts
     (matches ANY server.ts, even in wrong directories)

  ✅ MATCH_PATTERN: game-server/src/server\.ts
     (targets the specific architectural component)

  Overly broad patterns cause:
  - False positives (advisory fires when not needed)
  - Advisory noise (agent ignores repetitive false triggers)
  - Harder to distinguish which rule fired

  Before committing a rule, test the pattern against the codebase
  to verify it matches ONLY the files it should target.

  Learned during guardian hook implementation: pattern scope was too
  broad initially, causing unnecessary advisor output.
